label: central sleep apnea
definition: A sleep apnea that is characterized by a malfunction of the basic neurological controls for breathing rate and the failure to give the signal to inhale, causing the individual to miss one or more cycles of breathing.

parents.label: sleep apnea
parents.definition: A sleep disorder characterized by repeated cessation and commencing of breathing that repeatedly disrupts sleep.

parents.label: sleep disorder
parents.definition: A disease of mental health that involves disruption of sleep patterns.

parents.label: disease of mental health
parents.definition: A disease that involves a psychological or behavioral pattern generally associated with subjective distress or disability that occurs in an individual, and which are not a part of normal development or culture.

parents.label: disease
parents.definition: A disease is a disposition (i) to undergo pathological processes that (ii) exists in an organism because of one or more disorders in that organism.
